26/12/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska Prime Minister Milorad Dodik, leader of the main Serb Union of Independent Social Democrats (SNSD), predicted on Monday (December 25th) that SNSD candidate Nikola Spiric would be BiH's prime minister-designate. Negotiations among the major parties in parliament continue, aimed at forming a new state-level government. Spiric, incumbent Adnan Terzic from the Bosniak Party of Democratic Action, and Dragan Vrankic from the Croatian Democratic Union of BiH have been nominated to the post. (Nezavisne novine - 26/12/06; RTRS, Pincom.info - 25/12/06)
